# Copying Files and Folders

cp file1.txt file2.txt                     Copy file to another file.
cp file1.txt file2.txt destination/        Copy files to dir.
rm file*                                   Remove everything that start with the word file.
cp destination/* .                         Copy everything from destination to the current dir.
cp destination/* ..                        Copy everything from destination to the parent dir.
cp -r folder1/ destination/                Copy foler recursivly to desired directory.



